ciscoIetfMsdpMIB.name: ciscoIetfMsdpMIB
ciscoIetfMsdpMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 Tel: +1 800 553-NETS Email: q-multicast@cisco.com
ciscoIetfMsdpMIB.description: An experimental MIB module for MSDP Management and Monitoring. Version draft-ietf-mboned-msdp-mib-01.txt is ciscoized

cMsdpEnabled.name: cMsdpEnabled
cMsdpEnabled.description: The state of MSDP on this MSDP speaker - globally enabled or disabled. Changes to this object should be stored to non-volatile memory.

cMsdpCacheLifetime.name: cMsdpCacheLifetime
cMsdpCacheLifetime.description: The lifetime given to SA cache entries when created or refreshed. This is the [SA-State-Period] in the MSDP spec. A value of 0 means no SA caching is done by this MSDP speaker. Changes to this object should be stored to non-volatile memory. This object does not measure time per se; instead, it is the delta from the time at which an SA message is received at which it should be expired if not refreshed. (i.e., it is the value of cMsdpSACacheExpiryTime immediately after receiving an SA message applying to that row.) As such, TimeInterval would be a more appropriate SYNTAX; it remains TimeTicks for backwards compatability.

cMsdpNumSACacheEntries.name: cMsdpNumSACacheEntries
cMsdpNumSACacheEntries.description: The total number of entries in the SA Cache table.

cMsdpRPAddress.name: cMsdpRPAddress
cMsdpRPAddress.description: The RP address used when sourcing MSDP SA messages. May be 0.0.0.0 on non-RP's. Changes to this object should be stored to non-volatile memory.

cMsdpRequestsTable.name: cMsdpRequestsTable
cMsdpRequestsTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing group ranges and MSDP peers used when deciding where to send an SA Request message when required. If SA Requests are not enabled, this table may be empty. In order to choose a peer to whom to send an SA Request for a given group G, the subset of entries in this table whose (cMsdpRequestsPeerType, cMsdpRequestsPeer) tuple represents a peer whose cMsdpPeerState is established are examined. The set is further reduced by examining only those entries for which cMsdpPeerRequestsGroupAddressType equals the address type of G, and the entries with the highest value of cMsdpRequestsGroupPrefix are considered, where the group G falls within the range described by the combination of cMsdpRequestsGroup and cMsdpRequestsGroupPrefix. (This sequence is commonly known as a 'longest-match' lookup.) Finally, if multiple entries remain, the entry with the lowest value of cMsdpRequestsPriority is chosen. The SA Request message is sent to the peer described by this row.

cMsdpRequestsEntry.name: cMsdpRequestsEntry
cMsdpRequestsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a group range used when deciding where to send an SA Request message.

cMsdpRequestsGroupAddress.name: cMsdpRequestsGroupAddress
cMsdpRequestsGroupAddress.description: The group address that, when combined with the mask in this entry, represents the group range to which this row applies.

cMsdpRequestsGroupMask.name: cMsdpRequestsGroupMask
cMsdpRequestsGroupMask.description: The mask that, when combined with the group address in this entry, represents the group range to which this row applies.

cMsdpRequestsPeer.name: cMsdpRequestsPeer
cMsdpRequestsPeer.description: The peer to which MSDP SA Requests for groups matching this entry's group range will be sent. This object combined with cMsdpRequestsPeerType must match the INDEX of a row in the cMsdpPeerTable, and to be considered, this peer's cMsdpPeerState must be established.

cMsdpRequestsStatus.name: cMsdpRequestsStatus
cMsdpRequestsStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new rows may be added to the table or old rows may be deleted.

cMsdpPeerTable.name: cMsdpPeerTable
cMsdpPeerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the MSDP speaker's peers.

cMsdpPeerEntry.name: cMsdpPeerEntry
cMsdpPeerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an MSDP peer. If row creation is supported, dynamically added rows are added to the system's stable configuration (corresponding to a StorageType value of nonVolatile).

cMsdpPeerRemoteAddress.name: cMsdpPeerRemoteAddress
cMsdpPeerRemoteAddress.description: The address of the remote MSDP peer.

cMsdpPeerState.name: cMsdpPeerState
cMsdpPeerState.description: The state of the MSDP TCP connection with this peer.

cMsdpPeerRPFFailures.name: cMsdpPeerRPFFailures
cMsdpPeerRPFFailures.description: The number of SA messages received from this peer which failed the Peer-RPF check. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerInSAs.name: cMsdpPeerInSAs
cMsdpPeerInSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages received on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerOutSAs.name: cMsdpPeerOutSAs
cMsdpPeerOutSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages transmitted on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerInSARequests.name: cMsdpPeerInSARequests
cMsdpPeerInSARequests.description: The number of MSDP SA-Request messages received on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerOutSARequests.name: cMsdpPeerOutSARequests
cMsdpPeerOutSARequests.description: The number of MSDP SA-Request messages transmitted on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerInSAResponses.name: cMsdpPeerInSAResponses
cMsdpPeerInSAResponses.description: The number of MSDP SA-Response messages received on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerOutSAResponses.name: cMsdpPeerOutSAResponses
cMsdpPeerOutSAResponses.description: The number of MSDP SA Response messages transmitted on this TCP connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerInControlMessages.name: cMsdpPeerInControlMessages
cMsdpPeerInControlMessages.description: The total number of MSDP messages, excluding encapsulated data packets, received on this TCP connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerOutControlMessages.name: cMsdpPeerOutControlMessages
cMsdpPeerOutControlMessages.description: The total number of MSDP messages, excluding encapsulated data packets, transmitted on this TCP connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerInDataPackets.name: cMsdpPeerInDataPackets
cMsdpPeerInDataPackets.description: The total number of encapsulated data packets received from this peer. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerOutDataPackets.name: cMsdpPeerOutDataPackets
cMsdpPeerOutDataPackets.description: The total number of encapsulated data packets sent to this peer. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

cMsdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.name: cMsdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions
cMsdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.description: The total number of times the MSDP FSM transitioned into the ESTABLISHED state.

cMsdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.name: cMsdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime
cMsdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.description: This timestamp is set to the value of sysUpTime when a peer transitions into or out of the ESTABLISHED state. It is set to zero when the MSDP speaker is booted.

cMsdpPeerInMessageTime.name: cMsdpPeerInMessageTime
cMsdpPeerInMessageTime.description: The sysUpTime value when the last MSDP message was received from the peer. It is set to zero when the MSDP speaker is booted.

cMsdpPeerLocalAddress.name: cMsdpPeerLocalAddress
cMsdpPeerLocalAddress.description: The local IP address used for this entry's MSDP TCP connection.

cMsdpPeerConnectRetryInterval.name: cMsdpPeerConnectRetryInterval
cMsdpPeerConnectRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the [ConnectRetry-period] for this peer.

cMsdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured.name: cMsdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured
cMsdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the [HoldTime-Period] configured for this MSDP speaker with this peer. If the value of this object is zero (0), the MSDP connection is never torn down due to the absence of messages from the peer.

cMsdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured.name: cMsdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured
cMsdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the [KeepAlive-Period] configured for this MSDP speaker with this peer. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodic KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the MSDP connection has been established.

cMsdpPeerDataTtl.name: cMsdpPeerDataTtl
cMsdpPeerDataTtl.description: The minimum TTL a packet is required to have before it may be forwarded using SA encapsulation to this peer.

cMsdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom.name: cMsdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom
cMsdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom.description: This object indicates whether or not to process MSDP SA Request messages from this peer. If True(1), MSDP SA Request messages from this peer are processed and replied to (if appropriate) with SA Response messages. If False(2), MSDP SA Request messages from this peer are silently ignored. It defaults to False when cMsdpCacheLifetime is 0 and True when cMsdpCacheLifetime is non-0. This object is deprecated because MSDP SA Requests were removed from the MSDP specification.

cMsdpPeerStatus.name: cMsdpPeerStatus
cMsdpPeerStatus.description: The RowStatus object by which peers can be added and deleted. A transition to 'active' will cause the MSDP 'Enable MSDP peering with P' Event to be generated. A transition out of the 'active' state will cause the MSDP 'Disable MSDP peering with P' Event to be generated. Care should be used in providing write access to this object without adequate authentication. cMsdpPeerRemoteAddress is the only variable that must be set to a valid value before the row can be activated. Since this is the table's INDEX, a row can be activated by simply setting the cMsdpPeerStatus variable. It is possible to modify other columns in the same conceptual row when the status value is active(1).

cMsdpPeerRemotePort.name: cMsdpPeerRemotePort
cMsdpPeerRemotePort.description: The remote port for the TCP connection between the MSDP peers.

cMsdpPeerLocalPort.name: cMsdpPeerLocalPort
cMsdpPeerLocalPort.description: The local port for the TCP connection between the MSDP peers.

cMsdpPeerEncapsulationType.name: cMsdpPeerEncapsulationType
cMsdpPeerEncapsulationType.description: The encapsulation in use when encapsulating data in SA messages to this peer.

cMsdpPeerConnectionAttempts.name: cMsdpPeerConnectionAttempts
cMsdpPeerConnectionAttempts.description: The number of times the state machine has transitioned from INACTIVE to CONNECTING.

cMsdpPeerInNotifications.name: cMsdpPeerInNotifications
cMsdpPeerInNotifications.description: The number of MSDP Notification messages received from this peer. This object is deprecated because MSDP Notifications have been removed from the spec.

cMsdpPeerOutNotifications.name: cMsdpPeerOutNotifications
cMsdpPeerOutNotifications.description: The number of MSDP Notification messages transmitted to this peer. This object is deprecated because MSDP Notifications have been removed from the spec.

cMsdpPeerLastError.name: cMsdpPeerLastError
cMsdpPeerLastError.description: The last error code and subcode received via Notification from this peer. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the O-bit and error code, and the second byte contains the subcode. This object is deprecated because MSDP Notifications have been removed from the spec.

cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.name: cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime
cMsdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which one or more of this entry's counters suffered a discontinuity. See the DESCRIPTION of each object to see if it is expected to have discontinuities. These discontinuities may occur at peer connection establishment. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

cMsdpSACacheTable.name: cMsdpSACacheTable
cMsdpSACacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the MSDP SA advertisements currently in the MSDP speaker's cache.

cMsdpSACacheEntry.name: cMsdpSACacheEntry
cMsdpSACacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an MSDP SA advertisement. The INDEX to this table includes cMsdpSACacheOriginRP for diagnosing incorrect MSDP advertisements; normally a Group and Source pair would be unique. Row creation is not permitted; msdpSACacheStatus may only be used to delete rows from this table.

cMsdpSACacheGroupAddr.name: cMsdpSACacheGroupAddr
cMsdpSACacheGroupAddr.description: The group address of the SA Cache entry.

cMsdpSACacheSourceAddr.name: cMsdpSACacheSourceAddr
cMsdpSACacheSourceAddr.description: The source address of the SA Cache entry.

cMsdpSACacheOriginRP.name: cMsdpSACacheOriginRP
cMsdpSACacheOriginRP.description: The RP of the SA Cache entry. This field is in the INDEX in order to catch multiple RP's advertising the same source and group.

cMsdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom.name: cMsdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom
cMsdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom.description: The peer from which this SA Cache entry was last accepted. This address must correspond to the cMsdpPeerRemoteAddress value for a row in the MSDP Peer Table. This should be 0.0.0.0 on the router that originated the entry.

cMsdpSACacheRPFPeer.name: cMsdpSACacheRPFPeer
cMsdpSACacheRPFPeer.description: The peer from which an SA message corresponding to this cache entry would be accepted (i.e. the RPF peer for cMsdpSACacheOriginRP). This may be different than cMsdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom if this entry was created by an MSDP SA-Response. This address must correspond to the cMsdpPeerRemoteAddress value for a row in the MSDP Peer Table, or may be 0.0.0.0 if no RPF peer exists.

cMsdpSACacheInSAs.name: cMsdpSACacheInSAs
cMsdpSACacheInSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages received relevant to this cache entry. This object must be initialized to zero when creating a cache entry.

cMsdpSACacheInDataPackets.name: cMsdpSACacheInDataPackets
cMsdpSACacheInDataPackets.description: The number of MSDP encapsulated data packets received relevant to this cache entry. This object must be initialized to zero when creating a cache entry.

cMsdpSACacheUpTime.name: cMsdpSACacheUpTime
cMsdpSACacheUpTime.description: The time since this entry was first placed in the SA cache. The first epoch is the time that the entry was first placed in the SA cache, and the second epoch is the current time.

cMsdpSACacheExpiryTime.name: cMsdpSACacheExpiryTime
cMsdpSACacheExpiryTime.description: The time remaining before this entry will expire from the SA cache. The first epoch is now, and the second epoch is the time that the entry will expire.

cMsdpSACacheStatus.name: cMsdpSACacheStatus
cMsdpSACacheStatus.description: The status of this row in the table. The only allowable actions are to retrieve the status, which will be `active', or to set the status to `destroy' in order to remove this entry from the cache. Row creation is not permitted. No columnar objects are writable, so there are none that may be changed while the status value is active(1).

cMsdpMeshGroupTable.name: cMsdpMeshGroupTable
cMsdpMeshGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing MSDP Mesh Group configuration.

cMsdpMeshGroupEntry.name: cMsdpMeshGroupEntry
cMsdpMeshGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) repesenting a peer in an MSDP Mesh Group. If row creation is supported, dynamically added rows are added to the system's stable configuration (corresponding to a StorageType value of nonVolatile).

cMsdpMeshGroupName.name: cMsdpMeshGroupName
cMsdpMeshGroupName.description: The name of the mesh group.

cMsdpMeshGroupPeerAddress.name: cMsdpMeshGroupPeerAddress
cMsdpMeshGroupPeerAddress.description: A peer address that is a member of the mesh group with name cMsdpMeshGroupName. The cMsdpMeshGroupPeerAddress must match a row in the cMsdpPeerTable.

cMsdpMeshGroupStatus.name: cMsdpMeshGroupStatus
cMsdpMeshGroupStatus.description: This entry's status, by which new entries may be added to the table and old entries deleted. cMsdpMeshGroupName and cMsdpMeshGroupPeerAddress must be set to valid values before the row can be activated. Since these are the table's INDEX, a row can be activated by simply setting the cMsdpMeshGroupStatus variable. It is not possible to modify other columns in the same conceptual row when the status value is active(1), because there only other objects in the row are part of the INDEX. Changing one of these changes the row, so an old row must be deleted and a new one created.

cMsdpEstablished.name: cMsdpEstablished
cMsdpEstablished.description: The MSDP Established event is generated when the MSDP FSM enters the ESTABLISHED state.

cMsdpBackwardTransition.name: cMsdpBackwardTransition
cMsdpBackwardTransition.description: The MSDPBackwardTransition Event is generated when the MSDP FSM moves from a higher numbered state to a lower numbered state.

cMsdpMIBCompliance.name: cMsdpMIBCompliance
cMsdpMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement a pre- RFC version of MSDP. This statement is deprecated because it includes objects used for managing/monitoring aspects of MSDP that were removed before it was published as an RFC.

cMsdpMIBFullCompliance.name: cMsdpMIBFullCompliance
cMsdpMIBFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement MSDP (RFC3618).

cMsdpMIBReadOnlyCompliance.name: cMsdpMIBReadOnlyCompliance
cMsdpMIBReadOnlyCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement MSDP (RFC3618), but do not permit configuration (or only permit partial configuration) via SNMP.

cMsdpMIBGlobalsGroup.name: cMsdpMIBGlobalsGroup
cMsdpMIBGlobalsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information on global MSDP state.

cMsdpMIBPeerGroup.name: cMsdpMIBPeerGroup
cMsdpMIBPeerGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP peers. This group is deprecated in favor of cMsdpMIBPeerGroup2 because it contains objects for managing aspects of MSDP that were removed before it was published as an RFC.

cMsdpMIBEncapsulationGroup.name: cMsdpMIBEncapsulationGroup
cMsdpMIBEncapsulationGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing encapsulations if the MSDP encapsulation interfaces are not given interface indices.

cMsdpMIBSACacheGroup.name: cMsdpMIBSACacheGroup
cMsdpMIBSACacheGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP SA cache entries.

cMsdpMIBNotificationGroup.name: cMsdpMIBNotificationGroup
cMsdpMIBNotificationGroup.description: A collection of notifications for signaling changes in MSDP peer relationships.

cMsdpMIBRequestsGroup.name: cMsdpMIBRequestsGroup
cMsdpMIBRequestsGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP Request transmission. This group is deprecated because Requests were removed from MSDP before its publication as RFC.

cMsdpMIBRPGroup.name: cMsdpMIBRPGroup
cMsdpMIBRPGroup.description: A collection of objects for MSDP speakers that source MSDP messages.

cMsdpMIBMeshGroupGroup.name: cMsdpMIBMeshGroupGroup
cMsdpMIBMeshGroupGroup.description: A collection of objects for MSDP speakers that can participate in MSDP mesh groups.

cMsdpMIBPeerGroup2.name: cMsdpMIBPeerGroup2
cMsdpMIBPeerGroup2.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP peers.
